00:00:45.380 --> 00:01:11.530
No doubt every one of us at one time or another has faced a discouraging situation.

00:01:12.530 --> 00:01:16.530
Really, no one is immune from discouragement.

00:01:16.530 --> 00:01:24.530
This feeling may last for a day or two, and then subside or it might last longer.

00:01:24.530 --> 00:01:28.530
What can cause us to be discouraged?

00:01:28.530 --> 00:01:38.530
The Watchtower Publications Index lists over 20 factors that can contribute to discouragement.

00:01:38.530 --> 00:01:45.530
Some of these are another's conduct, what someone did or didn't do that disappointed us.

00:01:45.530 --> 00:01:52.530
Problems in our congregation, feeling inadequate, our own personal failures,

00:01:52.530 --> 00:01:59.530
what we've done or failed to do, health problems, and loss of privileges.

00:01:59.530 --> 00:02:06.530
There are ever so many things that can cause us to be downhearted.

00:02:06.530 --> 00:02:11.530
Even the fact that we are discouraged can be discouraging.

00:02:11.530 --> 00:02:15.530
We feel guilty for being discouraged.

00:02:15.530 --> 00:02:19.530
Here's the good news. We're in good company.

00:02:19.530 --> 00:02:28.530
Some very prominent and faithful servants of Jehovah mentioned in the Bible have been discouraged.

00:02:28.530 --> 00:02:35.530
Moses became so discouraged over the complaints of the Israelites that he said to God,

00:02:35.530 --> 00:02:45.530
please kill me right now. Rebecca was so distressed because her son Esau married pagan women.

00:02:45.530 --> 00:02:50.530
She told her husband, Isaac, I am disgusted with my life.

00:02:50.530 --> 00:02:57.530
Yes, family situations can cause discouragement.

00:02:57.530 --> 00:03:01.530
David was tormented by his sins.

00:03:01.530 --> 00:03:14.530
As Psalm 51 3 he wrote, I am well aware of my transgressions and my sin is always before me.

00:03:14.530 --> 00:03:19.530
Our mistakes can weigh us down.

00:03:19.530 --> 00:03:26.530
Jeremiah felt so discouraged by the opposition, ridicule, and apathy he met up with.

00:03:26.530 --> 00:03:35.530
He told himself, I am not going to make mention of Jehovah and I will speak no more in his name.

00:03:35.530 --> 00:03:41.530
Yes, poor results in the ministry can discourage us.

00:03:41.530 --> 00:03:51.530
The Apostle Paul, frankly admitted in Romans 724 and 25 that he struggled against sinful tendencies.

00:03:51.530 --> 00:03:55.530
At times he felt miserable over this conflict.

00:03:55.530 --> 00:04:05.969
He said, miserable man that I am, who will rescue me from the body undergoing this death.

00:04:05.969 --> 00:04:14.969
Faithful men and women faced discouraging circumstances in the past and so do we.

00:04:14.969 --> 00:04:21.970
Discouragement is a part of life in this system. We should expect it.

00:04:22.970 --> 00:04:28.970
Yet it's important to consider how we view discouragement.

00:04:28.970 --> 00:04:39.970
Do we view ourselves as helpless victims of discouragement and let ourselves sink into a quagmire of despair and self-pity?

00:04:39.970 --> 00:04:46.970
Or do we view discouragement as an enemy that we must fight against?

00:04:46.970 --> 00:04:54.970
We easily recognize that feelings of pride, selfishness, envy, and such things are enemies.

00:04:54.970 --> 00:05:03.970
We battle against these bad feelings. We don't want them to erode our faith or gain a foothold on our personality.

00:05:03.970 --> 00:05:10.970
Yet sometimes we may yield all too willingly to discouragement.

00:05:10.970 --> 00:05:13.970
Why is this dangerous?

00:05:13.970 --> 00:05:18.970
Please read with me, Proverbs 2410.

00:05:18.970 --> 00:05:27.970
If you become discouraged in the day of distress, your strength will be meager.

00:05:27.970 --> 00:05:31.970
Did you note the reason why we must fight discouragement?

00:05:31.970 --> 00:05:41.970
What do Proverbs 2410 tell us will happen if we allow a day of distress to discourage us?

00:05:41.970 --> 00:05:43.970
We'll lose our strength.

00:05:43.970 --> 00:05:53.970
Yes, discouragement can drain us of our spiritual, mental, emotional, and even physical strength.

00:05:53.970 --> 00:05:57.970
And what can happen if we lose our strength?

00:05:57.970 --> 00:06:00.970
We can lose our enthusiasm for the truth.

00:06:00.970 --> 00:06:05.970
We may lose interest in prayer or in personal study.

00:06:05.970 --> 00:06:09.970
We could slack off in attending meetings.

00:06:09.970 --> 00:06:12.970
We could develop coldness toward our brothers.

00:06:12.970 --> 00:06:16.970
Our zeal for evangelizing can weaken.

00:06:16.970 --> 00:06:20.970
We may even want to give up.

00:06:20.970 --> 00:06:25.970
We don't want any of those things to happen to us, do we brothers?

00:06:25.970 --> 00:06:31.970
How then do we fight and defeat discouragement?

00:06:31.970 --> 00:06:38.279
Discouragement is a feeling, an emotion.

00:06:38.279 --> 00:06:42.279
What causes feelings or emotions?

00:06:42.279 --> 00:06:54.279
An article entitled Negative Emotions, Can You Overcome Them, was published in the October 8th, 1992, awake.

00:06:54.279 --> 00:07:15.279
This article didn't discuss serious cases of depression that may have a medical or physical cause, such as a disease, a reaction to toxins, medications, nutritional deficiencies, allergens, hormonal problems, or bipolar disorder.

00:07:15.279 --> 00:07:27.279
Rather, it discussed how to overcome moments of discouragement, like the temporary day of distress mentioned in Proverbs 24-10.

00:07:27.279 --> 00:07:35.279
Under the subheading, we can control our thinking. It stated this.

00:07:35.279 --> 00:07:45.279
Many who work in the field of mental health maintain that our feelings are caused by our thoughts.

00:07:45.279 --> 00:07:54.279
It's been said that you cannot experience a feeling without first experiencing a thought.

00:07:54.279 --> 00:08:06.279
So then, feeling discouraged isn't always the situation that we face, but the negative thoughts that we have about the situation.

00:08:06.279 --> 00:08:15.279
The first step then in fighting discouragement is to identify the negative thoughts.

00:08:15.279 --> 00:08:28.279
Sometimes we say that we have a train of thought. It means we have a series of thoughts that lead to a certain conclusion or destination, if you will.

00:08:28.279 --> 00:08:35.279
Now, imagine yourself getting on a literal railroad or subway train.

00:08:35.279 --> 00:08:47.279
Soon you realize you're on the wrong train. It's taking you to a place you do not want to go to. What do you do? Do you stay on the train all the way to the wrong destination?

00:08:47.279 --> 00:09:01.279
Of course not. No, you get off that train at the very next station. But what do you do next? You switch to the right train.

00:09:01.279 --> 00:09:13.279
Now, figuratively speaking, if you realize that your mind is getting on a train of negative thoughts as leading to discouragement, can you get off that train?

00:09:13.279 --> 00:09:25.279
Certainly, but you need to switch to the right train of thought that will lead you to a peaceful state of mind. That's the key.

00:09:25.279 --> 00:09:33.279
We need to replace negative thoughts with positive building spiritual thoughts.

00:09:33.279 --> 00:09:46.279
Keeping our thinking on the right track is not going process. Notice how the Apostle Paul put it in Ephesians 4.23.

00:09:46.279 --> 00:09:54.279
And you should continue to be made new in your dominant mental attitude.

00:09:54.279 --> 00:10:08.279
Do you see how Paul confirms that we are in control? We can change how we think. And because we're imperfect, we have to make these changes continuously.

00:10:08.279 --> 00:10:28.279
It's not a losing battle. Jehovah has given us powerful weapons to help us make our minds move in the right direction, his powerful word, his mighty Holy Spirit, the power of prayer, and healthful spiritual food from his organization.

00:10:28.279 --> 00:10:42.279
Let's consider some negative thoughts that may lead to discouragement. Then we'll consider a building, positive thoughts that help us fight discouragement.

00:10:42.279 --> 00:10:57.559
You had a bad day. You said or did the wrong thing and you regret it. It's become a day of distress. The thought enters your mind. I'm worthless.

00:10:57.559 --> 00:11:08.559
That's the discouragement train where you continue to stay on this train of thought, taking you to the state of discouragement.

00:11:08.559 --> 00:11:23.559
Remember, you have a choice. You can reject it. Instead of giving in to that negative thought, you could say to yourself, wait a minute, stop.

00:11:23.559 --> 00:11:37.559
That's not right. Just because I made a mistake. Does not make me worthless in Jehovah's eyes? He's told us that he knows that we are dust and he's merciful.

00:11:37.559 --> 00:11:50.559
And Jesus said that not one sparrow that has fallen to the ground is forgotten by God. And that we are worth more than many sparrows.

00:11:51.559 --> 00:12:09.559
Yes, Jehovah views me as precious. How pray about this. And I'm sure he'll help me not to make that mistake again. Tomorrow will be a better day. Thank you, Jehovah.

00:12:09.559 --> 00:12:33.559
Let's take a second example. A brother has said something quite unkind to you. This has become a day of distress. The thought comes to your mind. How can a brother behave like that and still be in good standing? He's not a good example.

00:12:34.559 --> 00:12:51.559
Why don't the elders do something about it? Now that discouragement, speaking, calling for us to get on board, if we stay on that negative train of thought, we could lose our spiritual strength.

00:12:51.559 --> 00:13:08.559
But we still have a choice. What we replace those negative thoughts with positive ones. We could get our mind on a positive track by saying to ourselves something like this.

00:13:08.559 --> 00:13:32.559
Well, that was an unkind thing for him to say. This is not like him. Maybe my brother just had a bad day. He's as imperfect as I am. I've said unkind things too at times and have regretted it. He's probably feeling the same way.

00:13:32.559 --> 00:13:55.559
I remember Colossians 3.13 says that we must continue putting up with one another and forgiving one another freely, even if anyone has a cause for complaint against another. Well, he has given me a cause for complaint.

00:13:55.559 --> 00:14:16.559
But it says Jehovah has freely forgiven us. He has certainly forgiven me countless times. No, I'm not going to allow this to ruin our relationship. How can I help my brother? I'll pray for him.

00:14:16.559 --> 00:14:24.559
And I'll pray for myself that I don't hold feelings of resentment in my heart.

00:14:24.559 --> 00:14:47.559
Let's consider a third example. After years of hard work at your place of employment, your position has been terminated. You've lost your job. It's a day of distress. You're filled with anxious negative thoughts. How will I care for my family? What will the future bring?

00:14:47.559 --> 00:15:07.129
Why did Jehovah allow this to happen to me? Where will this train of dark negative thoughts lead you? Certainly, discouragement will set in and you will become spiritually weak and exhausted.

00:15:08.129 --> 00:15:35.129
You still have a choice. You can replace those negative thoughts with thoughts such as these. Okay, I've lost my job. What should I do? Stop serving Jehovah? No. Jesus said that we should not be anxious over material things because Jehovah will provide if we keep his kingdom first in our lives.

00:15:35.129 --> 00:15:46.129
He also said to keep our lives simple. You know what? There are things that we don't need. So that's what we do.

00:15:46.129 --> 00:16:03.129
Simplify our life and do more in Jehovah's service. Jehovah promises never to abandon us. I'll throw my burden on him and I know he'll help us make the right decisions.

00:16:04.129 --> 00:16:20.129
Brothers, we're living in the last days of this system of things. We'll have our days of distress. Sometimes these come because of our own imperfection or the imperfection of others.

00:16:20.129 --> 00:16:42.129
But we also realize that the devil wants to discourage us. Revelation 1217 tells us that Satan's great anger is directed toward those who observe the commandments of God and have the work of bearing witness concerning Jesus.

00:16:42.129 --> 00:16:55.129
The devil will try to take advantage of situations and problems that we face to fill us with discouraging thoughts and drain us of our strength.

00:16:55.129 --> 00:17:21.130
Now we stand at the very threshold of the new world. Let's fight discouragement with all the weapons Jehovah gives us. Continue to steady God's word, making it a part of your daily life. Pray incessantly to Jehovah for his powerful spirit. Keep close to his organization.

00:17:21.130 --> 00:17:33.130
